Tomdroid (WB3IHY personal fork)
Tomboy on Android
Copyright 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012 Olivier Bilodeau <olivier@bottomlesspit.org>
Copyright 2012, 2013, 2014 Stefan Hammer <j.4@gmx.at>

https://github.com/WB3IHY/tomdroid

This is a personal fork of the original Tomdroid project (originally hosted
at launchpad.net/tomdroid), modernized to build and run on current Android
versions. It's maintained for personal sideload use and is not published on
any app store.

What's different from upstream Tomdroid
========================================
- Rebuilt on a current Gradle/AGP toolchain (Gradle 8.7, AGP 8.5.2,
  compileSdk 34) instead of the original Eclipse ADT / Gradle 1.6 setup.
- Notebooks support, matching Tomboy desktop's system:notebook:<name> tag
  convention.
- The old floating system Search Dialog (unusable on modern Android) was
  replaced with a proper in-app SearchView.
- Security hardening: real TLS certificate/hostname verification for HTTPS
  sync (previously disabled), no more logging of OAuth tokens or note
  content, parameterized SQL in the note content provider, safe note
  filename handling for SD Card sync, and backups disabled
  (android:allowBackup="false").
- Follows the system day/night theme instead of being hardcoded to light
  mode.
- Various crash fixes found through on-device testing (cursor lifecycle
  bugs, missing legacy HTTP library declaration, connection/cursor leaks
  on sync, etc).

Requirements
============
- Android 7.0 (API 24) or later to run.
- To build from source: JDK 17 and the Android SDK (compileSdk 34).

How to Install
==============
Signed release APKs are published under GitHub Releases:
https://github.com/WB3IHY/tomdroid/releases

Note: this APK is signed with a personal key, not the original Tomdroid's.
If you already have the official Tomdroid installed (e.g. from Play Store
or F-Droid), uninstall it first — Android will refuse to install this one
over it due to the signature mismatch.

1- Download tomdroid-wb3ihy-<version>.apk to your device, or pull it with adb:
   # adb push tomdroid-wb3ihy-<version>.apk /sdcard/Download/

2- On the device, allow "Install unknown apps" for the app you're
   installing from (browser or file manager), then open the APK to install.

   Or install directly over USB with the device connected:
   # adb -d install tomdroid-wb3ihy-<version>.apk

   To reinstall/upgrade:
   # adb -d install -r tomdroid-wb3ihy-<version>.apk

How to Build from Source
=========================
1- Clone the repository:
   # git clone https://github.com/WB3IHY/tomdroid.git

2- Make sure JAVA_HOME points at a JDK 17 install, then build a debug APK:
   # ./gradlew assembleDebug
   The APK will be under app/build/outputs/apk/debug/.

3- For a signed release build, set these environment variables to point at
   your own keystore (nothing keystore-related is stored in the repo) and
   run assembleRelease:
   # export RELEASE_STORE_FILE=/path/to/your.jks
   # export RELEASE_STORE_PASSWORD=...
   # export RELEASE_KEY_ALIAS=...
   # export RELEASE_KEY_PASSWORD=...
   # ./gradlew assembleRelease
   The signed APK will be under app/build/outputs/apk/release/.

Usage
=====
On first launch, read "Tomdroid's First Note" for instructions on setting
up synchronization. Two sync options are supported:

- Online Synchronization: syncs against any server implementing the Tomboy
  Web REST API (e.g. a self-hosted grauphel instance). Set Service to
  Online Synchronization in preferences and provide the Server URL.

- SD Card: copy your Tomboy *.note files onto the device under
  tomdroid/, then set Service to SD Card in preferences.
  # adb shell mkdir /sdcard/tomdroid
  # adb push <note file> /sdcard/tomdroid/

Either way, hit the Sync icon on Tomdroid's top bar to synchronize.

Uninstall
=========
On your phone under Settings -> Apps -> Tomdroid -> Uninstall.
Or, with the device connected and the SDK installed:
   # adb -d uninstall org.tomdroid
